<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">“Our country’s fiscal situation is undoubtedly extremely poor, worse than Greece’s”. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Japan reported last week that its GDP growth shrank in the past quarter, with investors fearing a recession. On Monday, the cost of borrowing rose after yields on the 40-year bond hit highs not seen in 20 years. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ishiba was elected prime minister after pitching himself as a hawk aiming to curb the excesses of “Abenomics”. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">After the US debt downgrade, the USD v JPY could be a currency to watch over the coming months as capital flows could change. For the moment, the yen may drop to test the lows of last September.</span></p>
